{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3635493,"name":"Tio","username":"Tio","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/d2c977/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-05-25T16:04:26.155Z","cooked":"<p>We’re working on adding AprilTag-based autonomous to our 2025 robot using two PhotonVision ThriftyCams and an Orange Pi 5. We’re using PhotonLib version 2025.3.1 and a full-field AprilTag layout.</p>
<p>We’ve written a <code>VisionSubsystemFullField</code> class with two <code>PhotonPoseEstimator</code> instances (one per camera), using the constructor:</p>
<p>java</p>
<p>CopyEdit</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">new PhotonPoseEstimator(fieldLayout, PoseStrategy.LOWEST_AMBIGUITY, camera, robotToCamera);
</code></pre>
<p>The cameras detect targets successfully (<code>hasTargets()</code> is <code>true</code>), and we’re printing the best tag ID for each camera to SmartDashboard. However, we <strong>never receive any estimated robot poses</strong> — the <code>update()</code> method always returns <code>Optional.empty()</code>.</p>
<p>Things we’ve tried:</p>
<ul>
<li>Using identity <code>Transform3d()</code> for the camera position (to rule out transform issues)</li>
<li>Switching strategies from <code>MULTI_TAG_PNP_ON_COPROCESSOR</code> to <code>LOWEST_AMBIGUITY</code></li>
<li>Confirmed tags are visible in the PhotonVision web UI</li>
<li>Confirmed correct camera names</li>
<li>Confirmed <code>AprilTagFieldLayout</code> is loaded via <code>AprilTagFields.k2024Crescendo.loadAprilTagLayoutField()</code></li>
</ul>
<p>At this point, we’re stuck — we can see tags, but no pose is estimated. Has anyone else run into this with PhotonLib 2025.x? Are we missing something critical about how the estimator expects input or field layout?</p>
<p>Please see vision code below. Thanks in advance for any insights!</p>
<p>package frc.robot.subsystems;</p>
<p>import edu.wpi.first.apriltag.AprilTagFieldLayout;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose3d;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Rotation3d;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Transform3d;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Translation3d;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.smartdashboard.SmartDashboard;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.SubsystemBase;</p>
<p>import org.photonvision.EstimatedRobotPose;<br>
import org.photonvision.PhotonCamera;<br>
import org.photonvision.PhotonPoseEstimator;<br>
import org.photonvision.PhotonPoseEstimator.PoseStrategy;<br>
import org.photonvision.targeting.PhotonPipelineResult;</p>
<p>import java.util.Optional;</p>
<p>public class VisionSubsystemFullField extends SubsystemBase {</p>
<pre><code>private final PhotonCamera leftCam = new PhotonCamera("LeftCam");
private final PhotonCamera rightCam = new PhotonCamera("RightCam");

private final PhotonPoseEstimator leftPoseEstimator;
private final PhotonPoseEstimator rightPoseEstimator;

private final AprilTagFieldLayout fieldLayout;
private Optional&lt;EstimatedRobotPose&gt; latestPose = Optional.empty();

public VisionSubsystemFullField(AprilTagFieldLayout fieldLayout) {
    this.fieldLayout = fieldLayout;

    // Simplified transform for testing
    Transform3d leftCameraToRobot = new Transform3d();
    Transform3d rightCameraToRobot = new Transform3d();

    leftPoseEstimator = new PhotonPoseEstimator(
        fieldLayout,
        PoseStrategy.LOWEST_AMBIGUITY,
        leftCam,
        leftCameraToRobot
    );

    rightPoseEstimator = new PhotonPoseEstimator(
        fieldLayout,
        PoseStrategy.LOWEST_AMBIGUITY,
        rightCam,
        rightCameraToRobot
    );
}

@Override
public void periodic() {
    PhotonPipelineResult leftResult = leftCam.getLatestResult();
    PhotonPipelineResult rightResult = rightCam.getLatestResult();

    Optional&lt;EstimatedRobotPose&gt; left = leftPoseEstimator.update(leftResult);
    Optional&lt;EstimatedRobotPose&gt; right = rightPoseEstimator.update(rightResult);

    left.ifPresent(p -&gt; System.out.println("LEFT Pose: " + p.estimatedPose.toPose2d()));
    right.ifPresent(p -&gt; System.out.println("RIGHT Pose: " + p.estimatedPose.toPose2d()));

    if (left.isPresent()) {
        latestPose = left;
    } else if (right.isPresent()) {
        latestPose = right;
    } else {
        latestPose = Optional.empty();
    }

    latestPose.ifPresent(p -&gt;
        SmartDashboard.putString("Vision Pose2d", p.estimatedPose.toPose2d().toString())
    );

    SmartDashboard.putBoolean("LeftCam Has Targets", leftResult.hasTargets());
    SmartDashboard.putNumber("LeftCam Tag Count", leftResult.getTargets().size());
    SmartDashboard.putNumber("LeftCam Best Tag ID", leftResult.hasTargets() ? leftResult.getBestTarget().getFiducialId() : -1);

    SmartDashboard.putBoolean("RightCam Has Targets", rightResult.hasTargets());
    SmartDashboard.putNumber("RightCam Tag Count", rightResult.getTargets().size());
    SmartDashboard.putNumber("RightCam Best Tag ID", rightResult.hasTargets() ? rightResult.getBestTarget().getFiducialId() : -1);
}

public Optional&lt;EstimatedRobotPose&gt; getLatestPose() {
    return latestPose;
}

public Optional&lt;Pose3d&gt; getLatestRobotPose3d() {
    return latestPose.map(pose -&gt; pose.estimatedPose);
}

public Optional&lt;Pose3d&gt; getTagPose(int tagId) {
    return fieldLayout.getTagPose(tagId);
}

public AprilTagFieldLayout getFieldLayout() {
    return fieldLayout;
}
</code></pre>
<p>}</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-05-25T16:05:16.145Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":11,"reads":153,"readers_count":152,"score":90.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":502371,"topic_slug":"help-needed-no-pose-output-from-photonposeestimator-in-photonlib-2025-3-1","display_username":"Tio","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":28847,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/help-needed-no-pose-output-from-photonposeestimator-in-photonlib-2025-3-1/502371/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3635502,"name":"Nolan Barker","username":"therekrab","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/therekrab/{size}/248500_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-25T16:08:15.802Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="Tio" data-post="1" data-topic="502371">
