<p>This doesn’t seem right… Aren’t we in 2025?</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-05-25T16:08:15.802Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":106,"readers_count":105,"score":51.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":502371,"topic_slug":"help-needed-no-pose-output-from-photonposeestimator-in-photonlib-2025-3-1","display_username":"Nolan Barker","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65568,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming Lead, Co-captain | 3414 Hackbots"},"post_url":"/t/help-needed-no-pose-output-from-photonposeestimator-in-photonlib-2025-3-1/502371/2","custom_user_title":"Programming Lead, Co-captain | 3414 Hackbots","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3635506,"name":"Nolan Barker","username":"therekrab","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/therekrab/{size}/248500_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-25T16:15:11.165Z","cooked":"<p>Also, I’m not seeing a constructor in the docs for a <code>PhotonPoseEstimator</code> that takes a camera (<a href="https://javadocs.photonvision.org/release/org/photonvision/PhotonPoseEstimator.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">source</a>). Are you certain that you’re running the latest version of <span class="abbreviation">PV<template c